						develop or restore, to the maximum extent practicable, the functioning of an individual with pervasive developmental disorder or autism, and that meet all of the following criteria:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(A) The treatment is prescribed by a physician and surgeon licensed pursuant to Chapter 5 (commencing with Section 2000) of, or is developed by a psychologist licensed pursuant to Chapter 6.6 (commencing with Section 2900) of, Division 2 of the Business and Professions Code.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(B) The treatment is provided under a treatment plan prescribed by a qualified autism service provider and is administered by one of the following:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 4em;">(i) A qualified autism service provider.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 4em;">(ii) A
